  ⊑ docs.apocky.com                ← auto-built docs · per-project subdirs · /docs/labyrinth · /docs/cssl

§ MONOREPO STRUCTURE @ on-disk
  ⊑ ~/source/repos/Apocky-Hub/ (NEW root) ← apocky.com Vercel-monorepo
    ⊘ apps/
      ⊘ hub/                  ← apocky.com root · landing · about · navigation
      ⊘ labyrinth/            ← /labyrinth product-route (CURRENT cssl-edge migrates here)
      ⊘ cssl/                 ← /cssl product-route (NEW · auto-built docs · examples gallery)
      ⊘ blog/                 ← /blog · MDX-based · cross-project posts
    ⊘ packages/
      ⊘ ui-kit/               ← shared design-system · CSL3-aesthetic-anchor · components
      ⊘ auth-shared/          ← Supabase-Auth client wrapper · JWT-validation
      ⊘ stripe-shared/        ← cross-project entitlements client
      ⊘ telemetry-shared/     ← cssl-host-attestation client wrapper
  ⊑ apps/* are-Vercel-deployable independently OR-as-monorepo
  ⊑ packages/* shared-code · published-internally (¬ npm-public)

§ TENANT-ISOLATION PATTERN
  ⊑ EACH-PROJECT has-own Supabase-instance (data-isolation)
  ⊑ apocky.com hub Supabase = central-Auth + cross-project entitlements
  ⊑ JWT issued-by-hub-Supabase · ALL-projects validate-JWT against-hub-public-key
  ⊑ user @ hub-login → JWT-cookie · ALL-apocky-properties accept-this-JWT
  ⊑ per-project actions still write-to per-project Supabase · audit-emit · independent-RLS

§ SUPABASE-PROJECT-LAYOUT (Apocky's Oracle org)
  ⊑ "Apocky-Hub"           ← NEW project · centralized-Auth + cross-project entitlements + Stripe-checkout
  ⊑ "The Labyrinth" ✓ EXISTS  ← LoA-specific data · keep-as-is · LoA-route consumes-this
  ⊑ "CSSL"                 ← future · CSSL-specific data (forum · package-registry · etc.)
  ⊑ "DGI" / "OmniMind" / etc. ← future · per-project Supabase as-launches
  ⊑ Apocky's-Oracle-PRO scales · 2-free + paid-additional · current-tier supports

§ CRITICAL-RECOMMENDATION @ Supabase-strategy
  Q: should "The Labyrinth" project become "Apocky-Hub" OR stay LoA-specific?
  ⊑ OPTION-A : RENAME "The Labyrinth" → "Apocky-Hub" · use multi-schema for-tenant-separation
              ⊘ pro : single-Supabase-project · simpler-billing · faster-cross-project-queries
              ⊘ con : tenant-data-mixed · harder-to-isolate-on-breach · harder-to-scale-per-project
  ⊑ OPTION-B : KEEP "The Labyrinth" as-LoA-specific · CREATE "Apocky-Hub" as-new-project · 2 free-projects-allowed
              ⊘ pro : clean-data-isolation · per-project-rate-limits · easier-to-divest-individual-projects
              ⊘ con : 2-projects-to-manage · cross-project-queries via-API-not-SQL
              ⊘ RECOMMENDED : OPTION-B · clean-architecture · scales-naturally
  ⊑ Apocky-action : 15-min @ Supabase signup-2nd-project "Apocky-Hub" · same-recommended-settings (UNCHECK auto-expose · CHECK auto-RLS) · save-keys to ~/.loa-secrets/apocky-hub-supabase.env

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
§ SHARED-IDENTITY-LAYER (Single Sign-On across-Apocky-properties)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

§ AUTH-PROVIDERS @ apocky.com login-page
  ⊑ Email + magic-link (Supabase native)
  ⊑ Google OAuth
  ⊑ Apple OAuth
  ⊑ Discord OAuth (gamer-aligned)
  ⊑ GitHub OAuth (developer-aligned)
  ⊑ Email + password (fallback · 2FA-required)

§ JWT-FLOW
  1 user logs-in @ apocky.com/account
  2 hub-Supabase issues JWT (signed-with-hub-private-key)
  3 JWT contains : user_id · email · email_verified · projects-entitled-to[] · issued-at · expires-at
  4 cookie set @ .apocky.com (all-subdomains accept) · HttpOnly · Secure · SameSite=Lax
  5 user navigates-to apocky.com/labyrinth → JWT validated · LoA-entitlement-check · grants-access
  6 user navigates-to apocky.com/cssl → JWT validated · CSSL-public-access (no-entitlement-required)
  7 logout @ apocky.com/account/logout → JWT-cookie cleared · all-projects revoke

§ ACCOUNT-LINKING (cross-project)
  ⊑ user signs-up via Google → email-captured · linked-to-account
  ⊑ user later-adds-Apple-OAuth → identities-merged · same-account
  ⊑ user can-link multiple-OAuth-providers · use-any-to-login
  ⊑ unlinking-leaves-≥-1-provider · sovereignty-preserved

§ ENTITLEMENT-SHARING (across-projects)
  ⊑ purchases-in-LoA grant-entitlement-record @ hub-Supabase · key=(user_id, project_id, product_id)
  ⊑ each-project queries-hub for-entitlements · validates-against-Stripe-webhook-records
  ⊑ cosmetic-PORTABILITY @ where-makes-sense :
    ⊘ Akashic-Shrine cosmetic earned-in-LoA could-display-in-OmniMind-Home (if-OmniMind-has-Home)
    ⊘ Apocky-decides-per-cosmetic-class which-projects-share
    ⊘ players-discover-cross-project-portability via-/transparency/cross-project-cosmetics
  ⊑ separate-Stabilized-Essence per-project (each-game's-economy-is-its-own)
  ⊑ Aetheric-Shards POSSIBLY shared-across-projects (Apocky-decision · simpler-monetization-pool)

